## Usage with Claude

### Reading Issues

```bash
# Read a specific issue
Read docs/issues/33.md

# View all open issues
Read docs/issues/README.md
```

### Working on an Issue

1. Read the issue file: `docs/issues/{number}.md`
2. View screenshots (images are in `docs/issues/images/`)
3. Create a branch: `git checkout -b issue-{number}-description`
4. Implement changes
5. Reference issue in commit: `Fixes #33: Description`

### Syncing Issues

```bash
# Manual sync (run locally)
node scripts/sync-github-issues.mjs

# Force re-download all images
node scripts/sync-github-issues.mjs --force-images
```

**Note:** Issues are automatically synced via GitHub Actions when:
- Issues are opened/edited/closed
- Issues are labeled/unlabeled
- Comments are added
- Manual workflow dispatch
